            . I am a <rs id="t18311201-246-viclabel1313" type="occupation">widow</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18311201-246-victim1877 t18311201-246-viclabel1313"></join>, and live in Alfredplace, Bedford-square; this cloak and handkerchief are mine - I was in the chaise, returning from Vauxhall, about nine o'clock in the evening; the parcel was in the back of the chaise - I did not miss it till I got home; I know no thing of the prisoner.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's defence. I saw the bundle in the road, and the watchman came and took me; I never had it in my hand.</p>
